status: MARC21-007: Secondary support material of projected graphic
Type of material of the mount of a slide or transparency for a projected graphic.

scope note (en): Slides and transparencies cataloged from data sheets are assumed to have cardboard mounts unless otherwise known.

definition (en): Glass mount that usually covers the film base but should not be the primary support for the film emulsion.

scope note (en): Usually used to frame larger projected graphics which need better support.

definition (en): Metal portion is usually a frame that holds one or two pieces of glass to support the film base. Glass should not be the primary support for the film emulsion.
Synthetic material is usually used as a frame to hold one or two pieces of glass to support the film base. Glass should not be the primary support for the film emulsion.
Secondary support material varies for different items in a collection.
scope note (en): Typically this is used for groups of projected graphics on various secondary support materials.

definition (en): Secondary support material is not known.
Secondary support material other than cardboard, glass, synthetic, metal, metal and glass, synthetic and glass, mixed collection.
